sentences: Alexandra Madarang Ilacad (born 26 February 2000), better known as Alexa Ilacad is a Filipino actress, singer, dancer, vlogger and model.
She rose to prominence when she joined the kiddie gag show Goin' Bulilit in 2008.

Aside from that, she was often seen in the Philippine television playing minor roles for various seryes such as May Bukas Pa, Nasaan Ka Elisa?, A Beautiful Affair, and several episodes of Maalaala Mo Kaya.

During her stay in Goin' Bulilit, she was first paired with fellow actor Nash Aguas for the Goin' Bulilit Presents:
In 2012, she was launched as a singer in the group Tweens Of Pop together with fellow Bulilit stars, Angel Sy, Mika Dela Cruz, and Noemi Oineza.
2013-2015: Her Blossoming Career.

In 2013, She scored her first lead role as she was cast as Lexie Domingo in the second season of the youth-oriented comedy TV sitcom Luv U, the official starting point of her loveteam partnership with Gimme 5 member Nash Aguas, famously known as NLex.
In 2014, She and Nash Aguas were paired again to do Camille and Drew in the television series Bagito which was based on the Wattpad series of the same name by Noreen Capili.

After the break-up of her loveteam, she has taken roles for Maalaala Mo Kaya, specifically the episodes entitled Family Portrait  and Passport.

In 2019, She landed the role of Luna Dela Cuesta, the 'rich spoiled brat daughter of Vito and Tessa' in The Killer Bride, the drama series starring Maja Salvador, Janella Salvador, Joshua Garcia and Geoff Eigenmann.
In October the same year, She scored her first lead film in the Philippine Cinema through the horror film Santigwar under Horseshoe Studios and Reality Entertainment.
